^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|If you have 4-card support, raise to 4, regardless of how many points you have. This is clear Law of Total Tricks bid, since you know your side has 10 trumps. This is the same reasoning as your jumping to 4 with 5-card support when your partner opens 1 of a major. Occasionally, you might have enough for slam, but that is rare enough that it is not worth worrying about.|
